        <div class="grid-container" style="height:100%;">
            <div class="grid-x align-middle" style="height:100%;">
            <div class="cell">
                <h1>About Us</h1>
            </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        </div>
    
        <section class="content bg-yellow">
            <div class="grid-container separator yellow pt pb">
                <div class="grid-x grid-margin-x grid-padding-x">
                    <div class="cell medium-10 large-8">
                        <div class="sectiontitle">About Take Time To Think: A new safer gambling campaign</div>
                        <p class="intro">Take Time To Think is a national campaign to encourage the routine
    use of gambling tools as part of a safe and responsible gambling
    experience. It is aimed at everyone across the country who bets,
    plays or gambles online or in arcades, betting shops, bookmakers,
    bingo halls and casinos.</p>
                        <p>Take Time To Think follows on from the longstanding When The Fun Stops, Stop campaign.</p>
                        <p>It is managed by the <a href="https://www.bettingandgamingcoucil.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="external">Betting and Gaming Council</a>; the standards body for the majority
    of the regulated UK betting and gaming industry.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    
        <section class="content bg-black">
            <div class="grid-container separator black pt pb">
                <div class="grid-x grid-margin-x grid-padding-x">
                    <div class="cell medium-10 large-8">
                        <div class="sectiontitle">Take Time To Think: Frequently asked questions</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    
        <section id="faqs" class="content bg-white separator-previous pb">
            <div class="grid-container">
                <div class="grid-x grid-margin-x grid-padding-x">
                    <div class="cell twocol-medium">
                        <div class="faq">
                            <div class="faq-q"><span>What is Take Time To Think?</span></div>
                            <div class="faq-a"><p>Take Time To Think is a national campaign to encourage
        the routine use of gambling tools as part of a safe and
        responsible gambling experience. It is aimed at everyone
        across the country who bets, plays or gambles online or in
        arcades, betting shops, bookmakers, bingo halls and casinos.</p></div>
                        </div>
    
                        <div class="faq">
                            <div class="faq-q"><span>What safer gambling tools can I use and where can I find them?</span></div>
                            <div class="faq-a"><p>All licensed operators must offer players a range of safer
        gambling tools. The main ones are listed on our homepage
        and include the options to set deposit limits, set time limits,
        cool off and self-exclude to stay in control.</p>
        <p>All betting, gaming and gambling websites work slightly
        differently, but you can find the tools by looking in the safer /
        responsible gambling section of operator websites.</p></div>
                        </div>
    
                        <div class="faq">
                            <div class="faq-q"><span>Who manages Take Time To Think?</span></div>
                            <div class="faq-a"><p>The campaign was a commitment made by the industry, in consultation with independent organisations and backed by consumer research, to back safer gambling.</p></div>
                        </div>
    
                        <div class="faq">
                            <div class="faq-q"><span>What is the Betting and Gaming Council?</span></div>
                            <div class="faq-a"><p>The <a href="https://www.bettingandgamingcouncil.com" class="external">Betting and Gaming Council</a> is the standards body for the majority of the regulated UK betting and gaming industry, excluding the National Lottery. The organisation works with its members to drive high ethical standards, create a culture of safer betting and gaming and build public and institutional trust.</p></div>
                        </div>
    
                        <div class="faq">
                            <div class="faq-q"><span>How can I find out what other steps are being taken to encourage safer gambling?</span></div>
                            <div class="faq-a"><p>The Betting and Gaming Council has worked with members
    to publish five key safer gambling commitments. The most recent <a href="https://bettingandgamingcouncil.com/safer-gambling-initiatives" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="external">safer gambling initiatives</a> are also outlined on <a href="https://www.bettingandgamingcouncil.com" class="external">The Betting and Gaming Council website</a>.</p></div>
                        </div>
    
                        <div class="faq">
                            <div class="faq-q"><span>How does Take Time To Think work with other safer gambling campaigns?</span></div>
                            <div class="faq-a"><p>Take Time To Think follows on from the longstanding When
    The Fun Stops, Stop campaign. While a separate campaign,
    it builds on the themes of reflection from the <a href="https://www.begambleaware.org/betregret" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="external">Bet Regret</a>
    campaign run by BeGambleAware, a campaign targeted at
    young males who are frequent sports bettors. We wanted
    this campaign to incorporate a wider audience, which is why
    Take Time To Think has incorporated best practice in safer
    gambling to do so.</p></div>
                        </div>
    
                        <div class="faq">
                            <div class="faq-q"><span>What if I need more gambling help and support?</span></div>
                            <div class="faq-a"><p>If you are experiencing problem gambling or are
    concerned about a friend or family member, you can
    get free, confidential treatment and support from the
    National Gambling Treatment Service. This is a network
    of organisations working together to provide confidential
    treatment and support for anyone experiencing gambling-related
    harms, free to access across England, Scotland and
    Wales.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Contact the National Gambling Helpline free on 0808 8020 133</li>
        <li>Access gambling support - including the helpline, live chat and via <a href="https://www.begambleaware.org" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="external">BeGambleAware</a></li>
        <li>Access gambling support - including the helpline, live chat, help for young people and forum discussions via <a href="https://www.gamcare.org.uk/" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="external">GamCare</a></li>
    </ul>
    </div>
                        </div>                                                                                                
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        
